entries.femaleVariant: <kiroshi l="creo" o="Kitè zo li rete poze avek lapè." t="May his bones rest in peace." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Li te dènye nan nou ki te sonje lavi sou zile a." t="He was the last of us who remembered life on the island." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Anvan lanmè yo leve nan kòlè, li te lakay nou." t="Before the oceans rose up in anger, it was our home." b="" a=""/>
You are V? We have been waiting.
<kiroshi l="creo" o="E nou pa mete konfyans anko sou bagay vini soti nan deyò," t="And we trust no more what comes from beyond," b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Men kounye a san Michel, yon lòt chanjman ap vini." t="But now without Michel, another change will come." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Nou pase nan lòt bò a, nan Guinee." t="We pass to the other side, to Guinee." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Menm jan ak Agwe Arroyo, Michel mennen nou pase tout dlo mal" t="Like Agwe Arroyo, Michel led us across troubled waters." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Bondye avèk ou." t="God be with you." b="" a=""/>
You my contact?
Had to meet here? Not big on funerals.
You my contact? Someone finally gonna tell me about this job?
Who died? Got somethin' to do with the job?
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Bagay vin chanje, fason lavi nou pa ta janm menm bagay la." t="Then came change, and our way of life would never be the same." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="E nou pral pran memwa Michel avèk nou." t="And we shall take Michel's memory with us." b="" a=""/>
You think we put together this funeral special for you?
I'm just the man in the middle. You will learn more... soon.
Wanna talk with Brigitte.
This some kinda test?
You screenin' me? See if I came alone? What kinda chrome I got?
This some kinda test?
Wanna talk with Brigitte. She here somewhere?
Shopping center by the intersection – go to the butcher shop there.
Ask for Placide. He will tell you the details.
Whose funeral is this?
Couldn't meet somewhere else? Not big on funerals.
<mothertongue l="creo" m="etrange" b="Do not be frightened, " a=". Dis funeral is not for you."/>
Most people we work with we knew as babies. We know their angels.
You we do not know.
No.
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Pacifica vin nouvo zile nou an." t="Pacifica has become our new island." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Tout moun isit la te konnen Michel." t="Everyone here knew Michel." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Men nou siviv." t="But we have survived." b="" a=""/>
So that's how you do biz in Pacifica.
Damn, how'd you recognize me?
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Lakay pèp nou an." t="Home to our people." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="ekraze sou tè nou an. Non." t="crashing against our shores. No." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Nou grandi pi fò andedan." t="We grow stronger within." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="pou nou rive kay nèf." t="to a new home." b="" a=""/>
Interesting biz strategy ya got in Pacifica.
No details, no names. No one knows a thing.
Your name we know. That is enough.
What gave me away? It's the hair, isn't it.
We have had eyes on you since you entered Pacifica.
Makin' sure I didn't get lost?
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Ou ka di sa." t="Something like that." b="" a=""/>
